com.panviva.util.pgc.processing

Class DocumentPostProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.panviva.util.pgc.processing.DocumentPostProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDocumentPostProcessor

    public class DocumentPostProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDocumentPostProcessor
    This class manages all the details to convert a business filtered and transformed common object model (xHtml) document instance to the final SupportPoint importable xml output file.

      • sanitize

        private void sanitize()
               throws java.io.IOException,
                      java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Clean up the XSLT 2.0 generated xml to ensure the document is able to be imported into SupportPoint. This includes the following: - Convert all less than and greater than to symbols - Inline all image element references inside the parent objects element. - Filter out all xHtml namespace declarations - Remove all non-printable characters - Replace all less than @ less than and greater than @ greater then symbol references generated by the xls transformation with a single less than and greater than symbol. This was used to protect against double less than or greater than references in word documents. - Convert all "emf", "wmf" (vector graphic) image file references to png using the ImageMagick library.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Exception thrown while processing final stage xml file
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - Exception thrown if the input file does not exist

      • convertImageUsingImageMagickWrapper

        private java.lang.String convertImageUsingImageMagickWrapper(java.lang.String imgSrc)
                                                      throws java.io.IOException,
                                                             java.lang.InterruptedException,
                                                             org.im4java.core.IM4JavaException
        Private Method to convert EMF and WMF Vector Graphics images to png using the img4java library wrapper around the ImageMagick convert executable. If successful it returns the non-null full pathname of the png generated file.
        Parameters:
        imgSrc - Source location for the vector graphics image
        Returns:
        pngImgDest Converted png image destination
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Exception thrown if an error occurs converting the vector graphics image to png
        java.lang.InterruptedException - Exception thrown if the conversion process is interrupted
        org.im4java.core.IM4JavaException - Exception thrown by the ImageMagick wrapper class if an error occurs calling the ImageMagick converter.exe to convert from a vector graphics image to a png
